üìê Understanding the Steady Score

The Steady Score is a composite metric that identifies stocks with reliable, consistent growth over time. It combines two key factors:

Steady Score = (Consistency √ó 60%) + (Stability √ó 40%)

Consistency Score (60% weight): Percentage of months with positive returns

Stability Score (40% weight): Based on inverse of volatility (100 - min(volatility, 100))
